text: At 11 : 01 a. m. London time this morning, Kate Middleton gave birth to her third child, a baby boy. Royal press was stationed outside Lindo Wing, where Middleton and Prince William are due to come out with their new baby to introduce him to the press. The world ’ s media are gathered outside the Lindo Wing at St Mary ’ s Hospital ahead of the birth of The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge ’ s third child. pic. twitter. com / FLr1lL2AyT — Kensington Palace ( @ KensingtonRoyal ) April 23, 2018 But Lindo Wing, the maternity wing for all of St Mary ’ s Hospital hospital, was serving other couples too, including this man and woman who walked out the door with their new baby.
